   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Family Caregiver Respite</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Over the years, a diagnosis of Parkinson&apos;s disease takes a toll. For the person with PD, the changes are slow, yet unrelenting requiring constant adjustment and adaptation to diminishing independence.  For the families, this steady progression also takes a toll.  Spouses and other family members too often find themselves the single source of help and support for their loved ones. The Family Respite Program provides funds for qualified families to hire help so that they can safely receive help.</narrative>
  </description>
